    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-24T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-24T04:00:00-05:00" n="458"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4376: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                            type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-24T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 24, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 24—6:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. If and when you take action contemplated in your 19, February 20, 2 p.m.,
                        <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName> who returns this morning will
                    presumably notify Council. Would you contemplate authorizing me to make such
                    notification at the same time to <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName>
                    in writing as a further evidence of our desire to cooperate with the Council and
                    to keep it fully advised?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
